Adds runtime Windows host-OS detection to llvm/Support and logs it in the
clang/lld --version output. (The _WIN32_WINNT header handling these functions
rely on lives in its own patch, llvm-win32-winnt-guard.patch.)

  WindowsSupport.h / Windows/Process.inc: OS-version predicates built on the
  existing GetWindowsOSVersion() -- IsLegacyWindows / IsSupportedWindows /
  RunningWindows{2K,XP,Vista,7,10}OrGreater (8/11 already exist upstream) -- plus
  GetWindowsOSName(), a human-readable "Windows XP 5.1.2600"-style string. These
  read the ACTUAL host version at run time, for BEHAVIORAL gating and diagnostics
  only; they do NOT fix load-time static-import failures (see
  llvm-support-pre-vista.patch for those).

  Process.h: re-declares the two public entry points (IsSupportedWindows,
  GetWindowsOSName) so cross-platform callers (clang/lld drivers) can reach them
  without pulling in the internal, windows.h-heavy WindowsSupport.h. Guarded and
  defined Windows-host-only, so every caller wraps use in #ifdef _WIN32.

  clang Driver.cpp + lld MinGW/COFF drivers: print the host OS line in --version
  (#ifdef _WIN32). For lld this is done at the print sites, NOT inside
  getLLDVersion(), because that string is also embedded into output binaries'
  .comment section, reproducer archives, and dep files.

  Windows-host feature; unused on Linux/Mac hosts (Windows/Process.inc is not
  compiled there).

diff --git a/clang/lib/Driver/Driver.cpp b/clang/lib/Driver/Driver.cpp
index eb3f9cb..784c356 100644
--- a/clang/lib/Driver/Driver.cpp
+++ b/clang/lib/Driver/Driver.cpp
@@ -2352,6 +2352,13 @@ void Driver::PrintVersion(const Compilation &C, raw_ostream &OS) const {
   // If configuration files were used, print their paths.
   for (auto ConfigFile : ConfigFiles)
     OS << "Configuration file: " << ConfigFile << '\n';
+#ifdef _WIN32
+  if (!llvm::IsSupportedWindows()) {
+    OS << "Note: Unsupported Windows version: " << llvm::GetWindowsOSName() << '\n';
+  } else {
+    OS << "Running on: " << llvm::GetWindowsOSName() << '\n';
+  }
+#endif
 }
 
